{#
  ============================================================================
  TEMPLATE: observation-medical-test-body_fsh.twig
  ============================================================================
  PURPOSE
    A PARTIAL TEMPLATE — a reusable body fragment included by frame templates
    using Twig's `{% include %}` directive. It must never be rendered
    standalone; it is always embedded inside another template that supplies
    the `Instance:` header and the observation category.

    Currently included by:
      observation-resultslab-eu-lab_fsh.twig   (EU lab Observation)
      observation-medical-test-result-eu_fsh.twig (MedicalTestResultEuCore)

  PARTIAL TEMPLATE STRUCTURE
    This file does NOT begin with a `%%FSH%%` marker. It starts directly with
    FSH body rules (`* id = ...`) and HTML bag calls, continuing the FSH
    instance opened by the including template. The including template provides:
      - The `%%FSH%%` section marker
      - The `Instance:` / `InstanceOf:` / `Usage:` header
      - The observation `category` coding
    This partial then provides everything from `* id` onward.

    The file ends with its own `%%HEAD%%` and `%%HTML%%` markers, which
    effectively close the section structure for the combined output.
    `%%HEAD%%` is empty; `%%HTML%%` emits the body rows.

  FOUR-COLUMN HTML TABLE
    Column 1 — Test code display                   (always present)
    Column 2 — Observation value or "L"/"H" flag   (conditional on value type)
    Column 3 — Reference range or interpretation   (conditional)
    Column 4 — Unit                                (conditional on Quantity)

    The column 2 header is dynamic: `addHEAD_th(labresult.report|date('d-M-Y'))`
    — the report date is used as the column header, not a static label.

  VALUE TYPE BRANCHING — Quantity vs CodeableConcept
    The template handles two FHIR value types using separate conditional blocks:

    QUANTITY BRANCH (labresult.value.type == "Quantity" OR labresult.valueQuantity present):
      Dual data path via ?? operator: labresult.value.* OR labresult.valueQuantity.*
      Note on variable naming — the mapping to FHIR Quantity sub-elements is:
        * valueQuantity.value  ← labresult.value.value  (numeric measurement)
        * valueQuantity.unit   ← labresult.value.code   (human-readable unit string)
        * valueQuantity.code   ← labresult.value.unit   (machine UCUM code)
        * valueQuantity.system ← labresult.value.system (UCUM system URI)
      The `.code` and `.unit` variable names are swapped relative to FHIR's
      Quantity element names — verify source data mapping when integrating.

      Fallback: when value fields are empty but labresult.valueString is set,
      `valueString` is emitted instead of valueQuantity sub-elements.

      Reference range: when both .low and .high are present, a referenceRange[+]
      slice is emitted, and the value is compared numerically with Twig's `<`
      and `>` operators to derive an interpretation code (L / H) and HTML cell.

      Reference range text fallback: when only .text is set, a text-only
      referenceRange is emitted.

    CODEABLE CONCEPT BRANCH (labresult.value.type == "CodeableConcept" OR
      labresult.valueCodeableConcept present):
      valueCodeableConcept emitted from either value.* or valueCodeableConcept.*
      via ?? operator.

  EFFECTIVE DATE — DUAL RULE NOTE
    Two effectiveDateTime rules may both be emitted for the same resource:
      1. `{% if labresult.effective is not empty %}` — conditional on .effective
      2. Always-emitted: `"{{ labresult.date|date('Y-m-d') }}"` (no condition)
    If both `labresult.effective` and `labresult.date` are supplied, two
    `* effectiveDateTime` rules will appear in the FSH output — SUSHI will
    accept the last one. In practice, callers should supply only one.

  BODY SITE AND SPECIMEN
    Both are conditional:
      bodySite[+] — when labresult.site is non-empty.
      specimen    — Reference to a Specimen resource by UUID when labresult.specimenid
                    is non-empty.

  CSS CLASS
    Uses `hl7__eu__lab__report` — the EU Laboratory Report stylesheet.

  CONTEXT VARIABLES  (all supplied by the including template's caller)
  ┌────────────────────────────────────┬──────────┬────────────────────────────────────────────┐
  │ Variable                           │ Type     │ Description                                │
  ├────────────────────────────────────┼──────────┼────────────────────────────────────────────┤
  │ instanceid                         │ string   │ Resource id (from including template).     │
  │ labresult.report                   │ date     │ Report date; used as HTML column 2 header. │
  │ labresult.subject                  │ string   │ UUID of the subject Patient.               │
  │ labresult.subjectname              │ string   │ Subject display name.                      │
  │ labresult.code                     │ object[] │ Array of codings; only first is used.      │
  │   [0].system                       │ string   │   CodeSystem URI.                          │
  │   [0].code                         │ string   │   Observation concept code.                │
  │   [0].display                      │ string   │   Display text for column 1.               │
  │ labresult.effective                │ string?  │ Optional ISO 8601 effective date/time.     │
  │ labresult.date                     │ date     │ Report date; always emitted as             │
  │                                    │          │ effectiveDateTime (YYYY-MM-DD via filter). │
  │ labresult.value                    │ object?  │ Value as Quantity sub-object.              │
  │   .type                            │ string   │   "Quantity" or "CodeableConcept".         │
  │   .value                           │ number   │   Numeric measurement.                     │
  │   .code                            │ string   │   Human-readable unit string (see note).   │
  │   .unit                            │ string   │   UCUM unit code (see note).               │
  │   .system                          │ string   │   System URI (usually UCUM).               │
  │   .display                         │ string   │   Display when type is CodeableConcept.    │
  │ labresult.valueQuantity            │ object?  │ Alternative Quantity path (same sub-fields)│
  │ labresult.valueCodeableConcept     │ object?  │ Alternative CC path.                       │
  │   .system / .code / .display       │ string   │   CC coding fields.                        │
  │ labresult.valueString              │ string?  │ Fallback plain string value.               │
  │ labresult.reference.low            │ number?  │ Lower bound of reference range.            │
  │ labresult.reference.high           │ number?  │ Upper bound of reference range.            │
  │ labresult.reference.text           │ string?  │ Text reference range (when no low/high).   │
  │ labresult.reference.unit           │ string   │ UCUM unit code for reference range.        │
  │ labresult.site                     │ object?  │ Optional body site.                        │
  │   .system / .code / .display       │ string   │   Site coding fields.                      │
  │ labresult.specimenid               │ string?  │ Optional UUID of the Specimen resource.    │
  └────────────────────────────────────┴──────────┴────────────────────────────────────────────┘

  AUTHOR   KH
  SINCE    2025-09-02
  ============================================================================
#}

{#
  ── Resource id ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  The Instance: header is provided by the including template. This partial
  begins with the id rule.
#}
* id = "{{ instanceid }}"

{#
  ── HEAD bag: four-column table header ─────────────────────────────────────
  Column 2 header is dynamic — the report date, formatted d-M-Y.
  This is the only template in the project where a HEAD column label is a
  data value rather than a static string.
#}
{{ addHEAD_tr() }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Test") }}
{{ addHEAD_th(labresult.report|date('d-M-Y')) }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Reference&#xA0;Range") }}
{{ addHEAD_th("Unit") }}
{{ addHEAD_trend() -}}

{{ addHTML_tr() }}

{#
  ── Fixed status ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
* status = #final

{#
  ── Observation code (td 1) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
  labresult.code is an array; |first extracts the first coding. The code
  element uses [+]/[=] indexing (code is repeatable in FHIR Observation),
  with .text set alongside the coding.
#}
{# Use first coding only — HL7 EU HDR requires exactly 1..1 code #}
{% set c = labresult.code|first %}
* code[+].coding = {{ c.system }}#{{ c.code }} "{{ c.display }}"
* code[=].text   = "{{ c.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(c.display) }}

{#
  ── Effective date — dual rule note ────────────────────────────────────────
  Rule 1 (conditional): labresult.effective — emitted only when non-empty.
  Rule 2 (always):      labresult.date formatted as YYYY-MM-DD — always emitted.
  When both are present, two effectiveDateTime rules appear in FSH; SUSHI
  uses the last. Callers should supply only one of the two fields.
#}
{% if labresult.effective is not empty %}
* effectiveDateTime = "{{ labresult.effective }}"
{% endif %}
* effectiveDateTime = "{{ labresult.date|date('Y-m-d') }}"

{#
  ── Patient reference ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#}
* subject = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ labresult.subject }}) "{{ labresult.subjectname }}"

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  VALUE TYPE BRANCH A — Quantity
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Triggered by type == "Quantity" or non-empty valueQuantity.
  ?? coalesces the two data paths (value.* vs valueQuantity.*).

  Variable name mapping note:
    FHIR Quantity.unit (display string) ← labresult.value.code
    FHIR Quantity.code (UCUM code)      ← labresult.value.unit
  The source variable names (.code / .unit) are swapped relative to FHIR's
  element names — this reflects the upstream data model, not an error.
#}
{% if labresult.value.type == "Quantity" or labresult.valueQuantity is not empty %}
# value as Quantity

{% if labresult.value.value is not empty or labresult.valueQuantity.value is not empty %}
{# Numeric quantity value #}
* valueQuantity.value  = {{ labresult.value.value ?? labresult.valueQuantity.value }}
* valueQuantity.unit   = "{{ labresult.value.code ?? labresult.valueQuantity.code }}"
* valueQuantity.code   = #{{ labresult.value.unit ?? labresult.valueQuantity.unit }}
* valueQuantity.system = ${{ labresult.value.system ?? labresult.valueQuantity.system }}
{% elseif labresult.valueString is not empty %}
{# Fallback: plain string value when no numeric quantity is available #}
* valueString = {{ labresult.valueString }}
{% endif %}

{{ addHTML_td(labresult.value.value ?? labresult.valueQuantity.value) }}

{#
  Reference range with interpretation — both low and high must be present.
  The Twig < and > operators compare the observation value numerically with
  the range boundaries and derive an HL7 interpretation code (L or H).
  When the value is within range, an empty cell is shown (no interpretation).
#}
{% if labresult.reference.low is not empty and labresult.reference.high is not empty %}

* referenceRange[+].low  = {{ labresult.reference.low }} ${{ labresult.value.system }}#{{ labresult.reference.unit }}
* referenceRange[=].high = {{ labresult.reference.high }} ${{ labresult.value.system }}#{{ labresult.reference.unit }}

{{ addHTML_td(labresult.reference.low ~ " - " ~ labresult.reference.high) }}

{% if (labresult.value.value ?? labresult.valueQuantity.value) < labresult.reference.low %}
* interpretation = $v3-ObservationInterpretation#L "Low"
{{ addHTML_td("L") }}
{% elseif (labresult.value.value ?? labresult.valueQuantity.value) > labresult.reference.high %}
* interpretation = $v3-ObservationInterpretation#H "High"
{{ addHTML_td("H") }}
{% else %}
{{ addHTML_td("") }}
{% endif %}

{{ addHTML_td(labresult.value.unit ?? labresult.valueQuantity.unit) }}

{% elseif labresult.reference.text is not empty %}
{# Text-only reference range — no numeric bounds available #}
* referenceRange[+].text = "{{ labresult.reference.text }}"
{{ addHTML_td(labresult.reference.text) }}
{{ addHTML_td("-") }}
{% endif %} {# reference range #}

{% endif %} {# Quantity #}

{#
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  VALUE TYPE BRANCH B — CodeableConcept
  ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  Triggered by type == "CodeableConcept" or non-empty valueCodeableConcept.
  ?? coalesces the two data paths (value.* vs valueCodeableConcept.*).
#}
{% if labresult.value.type == "CodeableConcept" or labresult.valueCodeableConcept is not empty %}
# value as CodeableConcept

* valueCodeableConcept = {{ labresult.value.system ?? labresult.valueCodeableConcept.system }}#{{ labresult.value.code ?? labresult.valueCodeableConcept.code }} "{{ labresult.value.display ?? labresult.valueCodeableConcept.display }}"
{{ addHTML_td(labresult.valueCodeableConcept.display) }}

{% if labresult.reference.low is not empty and labresult.reference.high is not empty %}
* referenceRange[+].low  = "{{ labresult.reference.low }}"
* referenceRange[=].high = "{{ labresult.reference.high }}"
{% endif %}

{% endif %} {# CodeableConcept #}

{#
  ── Body site (conditional; FSH only) ──────────────────────────────────────
#}
{% if labresult.site is not empty %}
* bodySite[+] = {{ labresult.site.system }}#{{ labresult.site.code }} "{{ labresult.site.display }}"
{% endif %}

{#
  ── Specimen reference (conditional) ───────────────────────────────────────
#}
{% if labresult.specimenid is not empty %}
* specimen = Reference(urn:uuid:{{ labresult.specimenid }})
{% endif %}

{{ addHTML_trend() -}}

{#
  ── FHIR narrative ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  Both HEAD and HTML bags flushed — full headed table including the dynamic
  date column header. CSS class: hl7__eu__lab__report.
#}
* text.status = #generated
* text.div    = """
<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
<table class="hl7__eu__lab__report">{{ emitHEAD() | raw }}{{ emitHTML() | raw }}</table>
</div>
"""

%%HEAD%% {# ── Section marker — HEAD section intentionally empty for this partial ─ #}

%%HTML%% {# ── Section marker required by the FSH pre-processor ─────────────── #}
{{ emitHTML() | raw }}
